{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-04",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_04_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 4 - The Black Bird",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 7,
  "page_start_sec": 501.58,
  "page_end_sec": 742.92,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.737,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 501.58,
      "end": 502.7,
      "text": "You're good."
    },
    {
      "start": 502.94,
      "end": 504.08,
      "text": "You're very good."
    },
    {
      "start": 504.98,
      "end": 506.04,
      "text": "It's chiefly your eyes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 506.14,
      "end": 506.48,
      "text": "I think,"
    },
    {
      "start": 506.58,
      "end": 507.24,
      "text": "and that"
    },
    {
      "start": 507.34,
      "end": 510.16,
      "text": "throaty sob you get into your voice when you say things like,"
    },
    {
      "start": 510.48,
      "end": 511.26,
      "text": "Be generous,"
    },
    {
      "start": 511.52,
      "end": 511.68,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 511.8,
      "end": 512.448,
      "text": "Spade.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 513.58,
      "end": 514.74,
      "text": "She jumped up on her feet.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 514.92,
      "end": 516.88,
      "text": "Her face crimsoned painfully,"
    },
    {
      "start": 517.04,
      "end": 517.7,
      "text": "but she held"
    },
    {
      "start": 517.7,
      "end": 520.36,
      "text": "her head erect and she looked Spade straight in the eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 521.4,
      "end": 523.76,
      "text": "\"'I deserve that,' she said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 524.36,
      "end": 525.12,
      "text": "\"'I deserve it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 525.18,
      "end": 526.32,
      "text": "but—oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 526.52,
      "end": 528.68,
      "text": "I did want your help so much,"
    },
    {
      "start": 528.82,
      "end": 530.04,
      "text": "and I do want it"
    },
    {
      "start": 530.16,
      "end": 530.6,
      "text": "so much."
    },
    {
      "start": 530.96,
      "end": 533.04,
      "text": "And the lie was in the way I said it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 533.1,
      "end": 533.24,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 533.34,
      "end": 533.64,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 533.8,
      "end": 536.02,
      "text": "and hardly at all in what I said.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 536.54,
      "end": 538.16,
      "text": "She turned away from him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 538.28,
      "end": 539.98,
      "text": "no longer holding herself erect."
    },
    {
      "start": 541.44,
      "end": 543.84,
      "text": "\"'It's my own fault that you can't believe me now.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 545.216,
      "end": 547.74,
      "text": "Spade's face reddened and he looked down at the floor,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 547.9,
      "end": 548.32,
      "text": "muttering,"
    },
    {
      "start": 549.568,
      "end": 550.67,
      "text": "\"'Now you are dangerous.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 552.192,
      "end": 554.76,
      "text": "Bridget O'Shaughnessy went to the table and got his hat.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 555.74,
      "end": 557.36,
      "text": "She came back and stood in front of him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 557.46,
      "end": 558.14,
      "text": "holding the hat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 558.26,
      "end": 559.48,
      "text": "not offering it to him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 559.61,
      "end": 562.18,
      "text": "but holding it for him to take if he wished."
    },
    {
      "start": 562.74,
      "end": 564.46,
      "text": "Her face was white and thin."
    },
    {
      "start": 565.632,
      "end": 567.18,
      "text": "Spade looked at his hat and asked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 568.14,
      "end": 569.344,
      "text": "\"'What happened last night?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 571.072,
      "end": 574.48,
      "text": "Floyd came to the hotel at nine o'clock and we went out for a walk.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 575.25,
      "end": 577.26,
      "text": "I suggested that so Mr.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 577.42,
      "end": 578.3,
      "text": "Archer could see him."
    },
    {
      "start": 578.48,
      "end": 581.02,
      "text": "We stopped at a restaurant in Geary Street,"
    },
    {
      "start": 581.2,
      "end": 581.86,
      "text": "I think it was,"
    },
    {
      "start": 582.4,
      "end": 583.5,
      "text": "for supper and to dance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 583.7,
      "end": 586.58,
      "text": "and got back to the hotel at about half-past twelve."
    },
    {
      "start": 588.256,
      "end": 589.5,
      "text": "Floyd left me at the door,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 589.58,
      "end": 591.66,
      "text": "and I stood inside and watched Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 591.86,
      "end": 592.06,
      "text": "Archer"
    },
    {
      "start": 592.2,
      "end": 594.2,
      "text": "follow him down the street on the other side."
    },
    {
      "start": 595.34,
      "end": 595.68,
      "text": "Down?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 595.92,
      "end": 597.14,
      "text": "You mean toward Market Street?"
    },
    {
      "start": 597.82,
      "end": 598.22,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 599.43,
      "end": 601.36,
      "text": "Do you know what they be doing in",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 601.36,
      "end": 602.92,
      "text": "the neighborhood of Bush and Stockton"
    },
    {
      "start": 603.08,
      "end": 604.02,
      "text": "where Archer was shot?"
    },
    {
      "start": 605.536,
      "end": 606.86,
      "text": "Isn't that near where Floyd lived?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 607.58,
      "end": 607.9,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 608.12,
      "end": 610.06,
      "text": "It would be a dozen blocks out"
    },
    {
      "start": 610.06,
      "end": 611.86,
      "text": "of his way if he was going from your"
    },
    {
      "start": 611.92,
      "end": 612.68,
      "text": "hotel to his."
    },
    {
      "start": 613.38,
      "end": 613.78,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 614.22,
      "end": 615.38,
      "text": "what did you do after they left?"
    },
    {
      "start": 616.19,
      "end": 617.28,
      "text": "I went to bed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 618.6,
      "end": 619.3,
      "text": "And this morning,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 619.44,
      "end": 620.56,
      "text": "when I went out for breakfast,"
    },
    {
      "start": 620.98,
      "end": 622.62,
      "text": "I saw the headlines in the paper"
    },
    {
      "start": 622.78,
      "end": 624.96,
      "text": "and read about both of them being killed."
    },
    {
      "start": 625.984,
      "end": 627.52,
      "text": "Then I went up to Union Square,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 628.32,
      "end": 630.02,
      "text": "where I'd seen automobiles for hire,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 630.38,
      "end": 632.84,
      "text": "and got one and went to my hotel for my luggage."
    },
    {
      "start": 634.048,
      "end": 635.96,
      "text": "After I found my room had been searched yesterday,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 636.42,
      "end": 637.9,
      "text": "I knew I would have to move,"
    },
    {
      "start": 638.28,
      "end": 640.34,
      "text": "and I'd found this place yesterday afternoon."
    },
    {
      "start": 641.248,
      "end": 643.34,
      "text": "So I came up here and then phoned your office.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 645.2,
      "end": 646.08,
      "text": "\"'Your room at the St.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 646.14,
      "end": 647.84,
      "text": "Mark was searched?' he asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 648.71,
      "end": 649.06,
      "text": "\"'Yes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 649.06,
      "end": 650.23,
      "text": "while I was in your office.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 651.44,
      "end": 652.1,
      "text": "She bit her lip.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 653.28,
      "end": 654.86,
      "text": "\"'I didn't mean to tell you that.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 656.28,
      "end": 659.168,
      "text": "\"'You mean by that that I'm not to question you about it?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 659.9,
      "end": 661.08,
      "text": "She nodded timidly."
    },
    {
      "start": 661.92,
      "end": 662.62,
      "text": "He frowned.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 663.68,
      "end": 665.54,
      "text": "She moved his hat a little in her hands.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 666.56,
      "end": 668.2,
      "text": "He laughed impatiently and said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 668.992,
      "end": 670.68,
      "text": "\"'Stop waving my hat in my face.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 671.488,
      "end": 673.06,
      "text": "Haven't I promised to do what I can?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 673.89,
      "end": 675.54,
      "text": "She smiled contritely,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 675.72,
      "end": 677.18,
      "text": "returned the hat to the table,"
    },
    {
      "start": 677.28,
      "end": 679.24,
      "text": "and sat beside him on the settee again."
    },
    {
      "start": 680.62,
      "end": 681.04,
      "text": "He said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 682.22,
      "end": 683.5,
      "text": "\"'As for trusting you blindly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 683.78,
      "end": 685.24,
      "text": "I've got nothing against that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 685.36,
      "end": 686.84,
      "text": "except that I won't be able to do"
    },
    {
      "start": 686.94,
      "end": 689.02,
      "text": "much if I haven't some idea of what's going on."
    },
    {
      "start": 689.96,
      "end": 690.34,
      "text": "For instance,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 690.58,
      "end": 692.12,
      "text": "I've got to know something about"
    },
    {
      "start": 692.22,
      "end": 693.38,
      "text": "your Floyd Thursby.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 695.02,
      "end": 696.31,
      "text": "\"'I met him in the Orient.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 697.72,
      "end": 698.5,
      "text": "She spoke slowly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 698.8,
      "end": 700.44,
      "text": "looking down at a pointed finger"
    },
    {
      "start": 700.44,
      "end": 702.28,
      "text": "that traced eights on the seat of the"
    },
    {
      "start": 702.52,
      "end": 703.32,
      "text": "settee between them."
    },
    {
      "start": 704.54,
      "end": 707.94,
      "text": "We came here together from Hong Kong last week.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 709.08,
      "end": 711.16,
      "text": "He was—he had promised to",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 711.16,
      "end": 711.54,
      "text": "help me."
    },
    {
      "start": 712.54,
      "end": 715.24,
      "text": "He took advantage of my helplessness and dependence on him",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 716.36,
      "end": 717.0,
      "text": "to—to betray me.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 718.208,
      "end": 718.62,
      "text": "Betray you?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 718.72,
      "end": 719.02,
      "text": "How?"
    },
    {
      "start": 720.36,
      "end": 721.78,
      "text": "She shook her head and said nothing.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 723.072,
      "end": 724.88,
      "text": "Spade frowned impatiently and asked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 725.28,
      "end": 727.06,
      "text": "Why did you want him shadowed?"
    },
    {
      "start": 728.14,
      "end": 730.44,
      "text": "I wanted to know how far he had gone.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 730.77,
      "end": 732.98,
      "text": "He wouldn't even tell me where he was staying."
    },
    {
      "start": 733.68,
      "end": 735.82,
      "text": "I wanted to find out what he was doing,"
    },
    {
      "start": 736.22,
      "end": 736.92,
      "text": "who he was meeting,"
    },
    {
      "start": 737.12,
      "end": 738.08,
      "text": "things like that."
    },
    {
      "start": 739.4,
      "end": 740.28,
      "text": "Did he kill Archer?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 741.58,
      "end": 742.46,
      "text": "She looked up at him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 742.48,
      "end": 742.92,
      "text": "surprised."
    }
  ]
}